comments.body:
@lzybkr Ideally it would throw so it can be used as a parameter type and fail to bind when the file doesn't exist. It is to eliminate this logic which is everywhere:

```powershell
    param (
        [ValidateNotNullOrEmpty()]
        [ValidateScript({
            if(-not (Test-Path $_)){
                throw
            }
        })]
        [string]
        $File
    )
```

With this:

```powershell
param(
    [PSFile]$File
)
```

I believe a type is probably the best implementation. I don't think an operator would work for parameters? I do like the idea of an operator though for use in `if()`... even if yet-another-unary-operator would rustle some jimmies.
